SSA NIRP fault guidance
text: Alex Montironi stopped by ACR to give us a brief explanation of the NIRP permits that are associated with the cryomodules. More info to be given in a wiki, but this was the brain dump from Alex for now. Each cryomodule in linac west has NIRP permits that allow the SSAs to run. Each cryomodule has 8 permits (1 per SSA/cavity). The SSA permit is complete when one of two vacuum gauges on the SSA waveguide (on the gallery side) reads okay. When all 8 permits are complete for the entire cryomodule, the cryomodule gets a beam permit. Once you get all beam permits for all cryomodules, the BCS gets a permit. The displays for these are shown in figures 1 -3 below. Note: the PyDM screens aren't implemented for everything yet. To get to these displays, go to the SC LCLS Home -> RF -> relevant sector note: relevant sector = GUNB, L0B, L1B, L2B, and L3B If you get a PyDM display, click the "NIRP..." button. If you get an EDM display, the button to click on is called "NIRP Control..." Once you click the NIRP button, you will see the display in Figure 2. This shows each permit described above. To drill down to the gauges associated with a particular cryomodule, click the Gauges... button in Figure 2. This brings up the display in Figure 3. The display in figure 3, shows the status of each gauge. As mentioned above, there are two gauges per SSA. One of the gauges is on the waveguide next to the SSA, and the other is on that same waveguide, but near the penetration. Both gauges are in the gallery. If both gauges are red for a particular SSA/cavity then the parent panel (Figure 2) will not have a beam permit. If only one gauge is faulted for a given SSA, the cryomodule still has a beam permit. If a gauge has a red circle around a green dot, that means the realtime status of the gauge is ok, but there's a latching fault. If you hit interlock reset on the gauge panel (Figure 3) this will reset any latch faults. This does not require a hardware enable. Note: this interlock reset button is a global interlock reset for all gauges of linac west cryomodules. It's present on several displays. If there's a problem with a gauge (both realtime and latching faults) call Andy Benwell to troubleshoot it. If there's a problem with the IO communication status, communication with the PLC is faulted, or if several things are purple, call Alex Montironi to troubleshoot.

title: * Re: BAS Transition complete
text: We have now transitioned from using a BSY BAS, a Linac East BAS, and a Linac Middle BAS to a new framework that has a "LCLS-I NC Linac BAS" and a "FACET-II BAS". The LCLS-I NC Linac BAS part 2 includes content that was previously in the BSY BAS. The general BAS has been re-issued to list the new BASs and remove the old ones that are no longer in use. The new BASs do not have pre-running conditions that reference other BASs. Instead, there are new documents called BAS Item Lists (BASILs) that include sign off items relevant to a region (PPS certification, exclusion barriers, and shielding). The new BASs reference these BASILs where appropriate in their pre-running conditions. We have issued the following BASILs to support the new BASs: Sector 10 Injector, Linac Middle, Sector 20 Injector, Linac East, and BSY. The Undulator Complex BAS remains unchanged at this time. It was logged out of the old general BAS and logged into the new general BAS. The BAS Instructions document was updated to describe this new use of BASILs as part of the BAS document set. There was also a USI screening (screened negative as a USI) performed for this change to the BAS framework that allows use of BASILs. Please contact me with any questions regarding the new BASs or BASILs, and how they are used. The RSWCF application has been updated to include the new BASs in the list of BASs that can be selected to apply to a RSWCF. Please use the new BAS titles in any relevant RSWCFs that are opened, and stop using the old BASs in RSWCFs from this point forward. There is one existing RSWCF prepared at this time (but not in the work approved state) that is tagged as applicable to the BSY BAS. This is form #8550, which is currently flagged "DO NOT WORK APPROVE. Consult with ADSO before moving this to approval." As instructed in the form, please do not move it to work approved. text: We have now transitioned from using a BSY BAS, a Linac East BAS, and a Linac Middle BAS to a new framework that has a "LCLS-I NC Linac BAS" and a "FACET-II BAS". The new BASs do not have pre-running conditions that reference other BASs. Instead, there are new documents called BAS Item Lists (BASILs) that include sign off items relevant to a region (PPS certification, exclusion barriers, and shielding). The new BASs reference these BASILs where appropriate in their pre-running conditions. We have issued the following BASILs to support the new BASs: Sector 10 Injector, Linac Middle, Sector 20 Injector, Linac East, and BSY. The Undulator Complex BAS remains unchanged at this time. It was logged out of the old general BAS and logged into the new general BAS. The BAS Instructions document was updated to describe this new use of BASILs as part of the BAS document set. There was also a USI screening (screened negative as a USI) performed for this change to the BAS framework that allows use of BASILs. Please contact me with any questions regarding the new BASs or BASILs, and how they are used. The RSWCF application has been updated to include the new BASs in the list of BASs that can be selected to apply to a RSWCF.
